WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:24.000
WorkHub OS is shown with synthetic, resettable data. No real employee or production environment appears.

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:49.000
The seeded admin path opens the role-scoped operations dashboard.

00:00:49.000 --> 00:01:14.000
The task register is the manager-side source of truth for assignments.

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:38.000
The launch-readiness record exposes its assignee, assigner, priority, due date, and discussion.

00:01:38.000 --> 00:02:02.000
The employee dashboard confirms that login did not start activity collection.

00:02:02.000 --> 00:02:32.000
Work Mode explains the explicit, reversible session boundary before consent is given.

00:02:32.000 --> 00:03:02.000
Starting a session enables session-scoped activity. Calls request media separately and just in time.

00:03:02.000 --> 00:03:30.000
The employee sees the same manager-owned assignment and moves it into review.

00:03:30.000 --> 00:03:58.000
A safe progress update is persisted in the shared task discussion.

00:03:58.000 --> 00:04:25.000
The employee explicitly stops Work Mode before signing out.

00:04:25.000 --> 00:04:55.000
The administrator sees the persisted review state and employee comment.

00:04:55.000 --> 00:05:25.000
Tests, builds, audits, and scans support a local prototype claim—not production readiness.

00:05:25.000 --> 00:05:42.500
External providers, production operations, privacy approval, and credential rotation remain explicit gates.
